{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nS2 (68ef) folds `claimed_session` into compiled state, but a folded state key is only\nuseful if it is DISCOVERABLE on the read surface and DURABLE across compaction. This story\nmakes `claimed_session` a first-class, documented read field and proves it survives\nsnapshot/compaction round-trips (incl. the pre-feature snapshot case).\n\n## What\n- **MCP outputSchema (`src/rebar/_mcp_models.py`).** Add `claimed_session: str | None = None`\n  to `TicketStateOut` so `show_ticket`'s advertised outputSchema enumerates it (the\n  compiled-state schema `ticket_state.schema.json` and the generated `types.py` already carry\n  it from S2).\n- **LLM read format (`src/rebar/reducer/llm_format.py`).** Add `\"claimed_session\": \"csn\"` to\n  `KEY_MAP` so `to_llm` renders the value under the compact key `csn` when set (a `None`\n  value is omitted, per the existing convention).\n- **Compaction safety (`src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py`).** `process_snapshot` restores\n  `compiled_state` via its generic key loop — a POST-feature snapshot carries\n  `claimed_session` and is restored verbatim. Add a DEFENSIVE\n  `state.setdefault(\"claimed_session\", None)` after the restore loop so a PRE-feature snapshot\n  (whose `compiled_state` lacks the key) yields an explicit `None` (key-present) instead of\n  relying solely on `make_initial_state`, matching the existing `managed_refs` / `attestations`\n  snapshot-guard pattern.\n- **`show` JSON.** `rebar show` returns the compiled-state dict, which ALREADY includes\n  `claimed_session` (it is a state key) — no separate JSON-rendering change is needed; a test\n  asserts its presence for a claimed ticket.\n- **Docs (`docs/event-schema.md`).** Document `claimed_session`: the STATUS\n  `data[\"session\"]` → `state[\"claimed_session\"]` storage, the ordered resolver precedence\n  (cross-ref S1 / `docs/config.md`), the fork-winner gating, and the compaction / forward-compat\n  behavior (older clones ignore the additive key; pre-feature snapshots default to `None`).\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the MCP model field, the `to_llm` `KEY_MAP` entry, the `process_snapshot` defensive\n  guard + a compaction round-trip regression test (both directions), a `show`-JSON presence\n  test, and the `docs/event-schema.md` section.\n- OUT: the `list --session=<id>` filter — DEFERRED to a follow-up ticket (it expands the\n  CLI + MCP + `apply_ticket_filters` + `match_predicate` arg surface for optional value, out\n  of proportion to this story). Also OUT: multi-harness fields (S5 / c557), capture hooks\n  (S4 / S6). The record/fold path is S2 (68ef).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `show <id>` JSON includes `claimed_session` for a claimed ticket. Proof:\n      `pytest tests/unit/test_claimed_session_read.py -k show_json -q`.\n- [ ] MCP `show_ticket` advertises `claimed_session` in its outputSchema. Proof:\n      `pytest tests/unit/test_claimed_session_read.py -k outputschema -q` asserts\n      `\"claimed_session\" in TicketStateOut.model_json_schema()[\"properties\"]`.\n- [ ] `to_llm` renders the session under `csn` when set and omits it when `None`. Proof:\n      `pytest tests/unit/test_claimed_session_read.py -k to_llm -q`.\n- [ ] Compaction round-trip preserves `claimed_session` (post-feature snapshot), AND a\n      pre-feature snapshot whose `compiled_state` lacks the key restores to `None` without\n      error. Proof: `pytest tests/unit/test_claimed_session_read.py -k compaction -q` covers\n      both directions.\n- [ ] `docs/event-schema.md` documents `claimed_session` (storage `data[\"session\"]` ->\n      `claimed_session`, precedence cross-ref, compaction/forward-compat). Proof: a\n      doc-content test in `test_claimed_session_read.py` asserts the section names\n      `claimed_session`, `data[\"session\"]`, and \"compaction\".\n\n## Depends on\n- S2 (68ef) — the record/fold path; landed in this stack."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783542953131244001,"uuid":"b53bb433-2d32-4f7c-899e-2218e15b63e4"}